ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LOW WILL BE CENTRED IN THE DENMARK STRAIGHT 985.
A HIGH PRESSURE CENTRE 1033 IN THE SW APPROACHES WILL EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS
THE ENTIRE BRITISH ISLES. THROUGH THURSDAY AND INTO FRIDAY THE RIDGE OF HIGH
PRESSURE WILL BEGIN TO RECEDE SWARD AS THE LOW PRESSURE IN THE DENMARK STRAIGHT
MIGRATES EWARD AND ELONGATES CREATING A SECONDARY LOW PRESSURE CENTRE IN
THE ARCTIC OCEAN WITH BOTH CENTRES DPN TO 980 BY FRIDAY AFTERNOON. BY SATURDAY
MORNING THE LOW PRESSURES IN THE N WILL COMBINE FLN AS THEY MOV INTO THE
NORWEGIAN BASIN TO 995. THESE WILL BE FOLLOWED BY ANOTHER LOW PRESSURE ARRIVING
IN THE DENMARK STRAIGHT 980 WITH HIGH PRESSURE BLDN ACROSS THE S OF THE
